                        "description": "A total of 175-\u00b5l methanol/chloroform (3:1) and internal standard solution (10 \u00b5l of p-chlorophenylalanine in water, 0.1 mg/ml) was added to 10 mg of caecal content sample, homogenized for 5 min and centrifuged at 13,200 x g at 4 \u00baC for 15 min. An aliquot of 200-\u00b5l supernatant was transfered to a GC sampling vial and vacuum dried for further TMS derivatization. A 50-\u00b5l of methoxyamine (15 mg/ml in pyridine) was added to the dried sample, and the sample was maintained at 30 \u00b0C for 1.5 hr. A 50-\u00b5l of BSTFA (containing 1% TMCS) was added and the sample was kept at 70 \u00b0C for 1 hr. The sample was votexed for 10 s prior to analysis.",
